news.title: PMAY funds siphoned off in Odisha, Chhattisgarh & West Bengal: Centre
news.para: The ministry has found that bank accounts of 60% of the beneficiaries of PMAY (Rural) in Odisha have been changed from the accounts furnished at the time of survey.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to auction 154 properties
news.para: Even as the housing board has decided to auction its 154 properties, disposing of the 99 leasehold commercial properties remains a challenge for the authority.

news.title: Indore civic body claims 80,000 rainwater harvesting systems, actual count only 30,000
news.para: While civic body authorities claim to have equipped and tagged over 82,274 individual houses and apartment buildings with rainwater harvesting systems, the actual count is only around 30,000, said official sources.

news.title: Bengaluru: Survey to identify encroachments in Rainbow Drive Layout under way
news.para: The layout was flooded following heavy rain last week, even as residents hired a tractor to ferry schoolkids. The residents had accused neighbouring villagers of diverting rainwater into their layout by breaching a wall upstream.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body, Auda & Guda to raise Rs 1,000 crore via land sale
news.para: The three civic authorities will sell a total of 23 plots totalling 1.38 lakh square metres. Authorities are expecting to raise Rs 1,000 crore through this land sale.

news.title: Gurugram: Remove encroachments from common areas of Mapsko Casabella in a month, says DTCP
news.para: This comes nearly three years after Casabella residents had filed a complaint at CM window against the developer for allegedly selling to gullible buyers the society's green areas which are part of the common areas.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills reports Rs 718 crore net profit in April-June 2022
news.para: Income from operations for the quarter rose 181% from a year ago to Rs 574.4 crore, while operating profit witnessed 324% jump to Rs 322.9 crore.

news.title: Citicorp Services India renews lease of 160,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai
news.para: The company has renewed the lease for the office space spread over six floors for a term of five years with a lock-in until September 2024.

news.title: SC exempts buildings up to 1 7. 5 metre tall with stilts from Delhi fire rules
news.para: A bench of Justice Indira Banerjee and Justice V Ramasubramanian said the 15-metre limit would apply to buildings without stilts, while buildings with stilts can be as tall as 17.5 metre, and any building above 17.5 metre would come in the category of high rise.

news.title: Noida authority to recover 'time extension charges' from Jaypee projects
news.para: While all developers paid time extension charges, this rule was earlier not applicable to Jaypee due to an agreement with Noida Authority. But board approval was sought to bring Jaypee within the ambit of time extension charges for the first time.

news.title: Land rates to go up in Noida after first hike since 2019
news.para: The land rate for residential sectors in the A+ category sectors remained unchanged at Rs 1.75 lakh per sqm. The price of plots in the E category sectors was increased to Rs 41,250 per sqm from Rs 36,200.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing puts sale of old ADAG property in Mumbai on hold
news.para: ​However, Piramal Capital & Housing Finance, which had put the tower and the 1.4-acre plot for sale, has put it on hold and informed builders privately it is no longer on the block, TOI has learned.

news.title: Emami promoters eye sale of realty, hospital assets
news.para: The promoters — Agarwal and Goenka families — own 54.27% in the company. About 32% of the promoter shareholding is currently pledged.

news.title: CBRI gives approval for rigging of Supertech twin towers with explosives
news.para: The nod of the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) was the last approval needed for the charging -- rigging of explosives inside the structures -- of the twin towers located in Sector 93B here, they said.

news.title: New Zealand house prices fall on year for first time sine 2011
news.para: The seasonally adjusted median nationwide house value in July fell 2.8% compared with the previous month and was down 1.6% year-on-year, according to REINZ. The unadjusted median house price was down 1.8% on year.
